    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Part 2: ML Advanced Univariate Volatility Modelling**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WnABzRBjVWWA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Feature Engineering and Scaling**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "idpEfo3jYhxN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Transform and create NUMERICAL features:***"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n_OqzTCfUuH4"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "At the moment we only have our realised variance (`rv5_var`) ($RV_5$) (1) and daily vix squared(`vix_squared`) ($VIX^2$) (2); neither can directly appear as a feature as they are not lagged and cannot serve a predictive purpose. Therefore, we will:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Create our target variable y = `log_rv5_var` = log($RV_5$) (3)  \n",
        "2.   Create our features X =  `lag_log_rv5_var` and `lag_log_vix_squared` = taking a variety lags of  log($RV_5$) and log($VIX^2$)\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Yy1sag5S3ciR"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "We proceed to take the natural log `log_rv5_var` of the series seies of realised variance `rv5_var` as this will become our target variable."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8G3b5tZ7VdJg"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df['log_rv5_var'] = np.log(df['rv5_var'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RM-miRTCVwo9"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Take the natural log of the daily VIX squared `log_vix_squared`."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "TOiZT2qaRyGJ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df['log_vix_squared'] = np.log(df['vix_squared'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "21x_fJIRkgAZ"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Why did we take the natural logs?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uKcPeTsMXRXL"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "fig = make_subplots(\n",
        "    rows=1, cols=2,\n",
        "    subplot_titles=[\n",
        "        'RV<sub>5</sub> vs. log(RV<sub>5</sub>)',\n",
        "        'VIX<sup>2</sup> vs. log(VIX<sup>2</sup>)'\n",
        "    ]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# RV_5 histogram\n",
        "fig.add_trace(\n",
        "    go.Histogram(\n",
        "        x=df['rv5_var'],\n",
        "        name='RV<sub>5</sub>',\n",
        "        opacity=0.6,\n",
        "        nbinsx=50\n",
        "    ),\n",
        "    row=1, col=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# log RV_5 histogram\n",
        "fig.add_trace(\n",
        "    go.Histogram(\n",
        "        x=df['log_rv5_var'],\n",
        "        name='log RV<sub>5</sub>',\n",
        "        opacity=0.6,\n",
        "        nbinsx=50\n",
        "    ),\n",
        "    row=1, col=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# VIX^2 histogram\n",
        "fig.add_trace(\n",
        "    go.Histogram(\n",
        "        x=df['vix_squared'],\n",
        "        name='VIX<sup>2</sup>',\n",
        "        opacity=0.6,\n",
        "        nbinsx=50\n",
        "    ),\n",
        "    row=1, col=2\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# log VIX^2 histogram\n",
        "fig.add_trace(\n",
        "    go.Histogram(\n",
        "        x=df['log_vix_squared'],\n",
        "        name='log VIX<sup>2</sup>',\n",
        "        opacity=0.6,\n",
        "        nbinsx=50\n",
        "    ),\n",
        "    row=1, col=2\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Layout styling\n",
